    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="730"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-15T23:00:00+00:00"
                            >September 15, 1936—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 16—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. Department’s telegram No. 125, September 14, 6 p.m. Americans are being
                    informed that Embassy will be closed as a place of refuge Tuesday, September 22,
                    and that those wishing to take advantage of final opportunity to leave Spain
                    will be evacuated from Alicante on the <hi rend="italic">Quincy</hi> next
                    Saturday. I have asked <hi rend="italic">Quincy</hi> to be at Alicante Saturday
                    morning. Destitute Americans will be evacuated in accordance with instructions
                    Department’s telegram No. 124, September 14, 4 p.m.<note n="39"
                        xml:id="d730fn39">Not printed; the Embassy was authorized to draw on $300
                        Red Cross fund. The amount drawn was $133.79. (352.1115/1455)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wendelin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
